layout.p:
Columns: 82;
                                                  ruled lines: 48;
                                                  written lines: 48; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point.Visible pricking and stiching. 82 columns in total, one to four columns per membrane. Three tagin on the letters שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהי. The letter ח is arched throughout, and פ' לפוף is very frequent.  Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. Special shapes of the letters ם, ה, ו, י. The "puncta extraordinaria" occur in Num. 3:39, 9:10, and 21:30. No inverted nun placed before and after Num. 10:35-36. Every column begins with a new verse, and the initial letter is always ו, with the exception of Gen. 1:1, 5:1, and 13 other instances.
